        <title>Configuration</title>
        <paragraph>To configure your Compute installation, you must define configuration options
            in these files:</paragraph>
        <bullet_list bullet="*">
            <list_item>
                <paragraph><literal>nova.conf</literal> contains most of the Compute configuration options and resides
                    in the <literal>/etc/nova</literal> directory.</paragraph>
            </list_item>
            <list_item>
                <paragraph><literal>api-paste.ini</literal> defines Compute limits and resides in the <literal>/etc/nova</literal>
                    directory.</paragraph>
            </list_item>
            <list_item>
                <paragraph>Configuration files for related services, such as the Image and Identity
                    services.</paragraph>
